result.execSummary:
The defendant David D. Alexander was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Attempt Theft-Movable Property >$2500-$5000 [Modifiers: as a Party to a Crime], a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Felony, a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(b).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Court calls cases 15CF89,15CF88,15CF37, 15CF115, 14CM89, and 15CM86.  Defendant David D. Alexander in court with attorney Alec Phillip Nocco.  Defendant David D. Alexander in custody.  Kristi S. Tlusty appeared for the State of Wisconsin.   Atty Tlusty states agreement on the record.  Victim rights complied.  Waiver of preliminary hearing filed.  Court questions DE. DE freely and voluntarily waives right to preliminary hearing. Information filed.  DE entered a plea of no contest to Cts. 1, 3 & 5 for 15CF88; plea of no contest to Ct. 2 for 14CM99; plea of no contest to Cts. 1, 6 & 8 for 15CF115; plea of no contest to Cts. 1 & 2 for 15CF89;  Plea colloquy.  Court found plea given freely, voluntarily, and intelligently. Factual basis exists.  Court dismissed, but read in 15CM86 and 15CF37.  Argument on jail sentence and expungement.  15CF88 - Court finds DE guilty of Counts 2, 3 & 5 and orders a withheld sentence:  DE placed on probation for 2 years on Ct. 2 and 3 years on Cts. 3 & 5 with conditions of: Court costs on each count; DNA sample and surcharge; 9 months county jail with Huber on Ct. 5; AODA and follow all treatment recommendations; Random drug screens, at the discretion of agent; Counseling as deemed appropriate by agent; obtain GED/HSED, at discretion of agent. Court dismissed, but read in Cts. 1, 4 & 6.  14CM99 - Court finds DE guilty on Ct. 2 and orders a withheld sentence:  DE placed on probation for 1 year with conditions of: Court costs; Service of process fees of $26.14; DNA surcharge; AODA and follow all treatment recommendations; Letter of apology to victim due within 30 days and pre-approved by agent; random drug screens, at the discretion of agent; counseling as deemed appropriate  by agent; obtain GED/HSED at discretion of agent.  Court dismissed, but read in Ct. 1. 15CM89 - Court finds DE guilty on Ct. 1 & 2 and orders a withheld sentence :  DE placed on probation for 1 year on Ct. 1 and 3 yrs on Ct. 2 with conditions of: court costs on each count; DNA sample and surcharge; restitution, joint and several with surcharge; AODA and follow all treatment recommendations; letter of apology to victim due within 30 days and preapproved by agent; counseling as deemed appropriate  by the agent; obtain GED/HSED, at the discretion of agent. Court dismissed, but read in Ct. 3.  15CF115 - Court finds DE guilty of Cts. 1, 6 & 8 and orders a withheld sentence:  DE placed on probation for 2 years with conditions of: court costs on each count; DNA sample and surcharge; counseling as deemed appropriate by agent.  Court dismissed, but read in Cts. 2, 3, 4, 5 & 7.  Court directs that DE may petition for expungement.  Atty Nocco will notify the court by letter on sentence credit. - ba
